ractions with pigeons offer surprising insights into city life, community, culture, and politics. Theoretically understated and accessible to interested readers of all stripes, The Global Pigeon is one of the best and most original ethnographies to be published in decades.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aHuman-animal relationships -- Social aspects. 0aHuman-animal relationshipsxSocial aspects. 0aRacing pigeons -- Habitat. 0aRacing pigeons -- Social aspects. 0aRacing pigeonsxHabitat. 0aRacing pigeonsxSocial aspects. 7aNATURE / General.2bisacsh  apigeon, city, urban, brooklyn, new york, south africa, race, sport, venice, piazza san marco, london, trafalgar square, berlin, working class, immigrant, community, breeders, culture, politics, habitat, human-animal relationships, greenwich village, sociability, nonfiction, carnism, birds, globalization, history, ethnography, sociology, poverty, coops, gentrification.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311063538640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226001920423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226001920/original  a978-3-11-063538-6  University of Chicago Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles